<h2>Solar Incentives in Denver</h2>
<p>Denver residents can take advantage of several substantial solar incentives that make installation more affordable. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, reducing a \$20,000 system cost to \$14,000. Colorado offers additional state tax credits up to \$5,000 for residential solar installations, further reducing the net cost. Xcel Energy provides solar rebates through their Solar*Rewards program, offering upfront rebates based on system size and performance. The utility also offers net metering, allowing homeowners to sell excess solar energy back to the grid at retail rates, effectively spinning their electric meter backwards during peak production hours. These combined incentives can reduce the total cost of a solar installation by 40-50%, making solar energy highly affordable for Denver homeowners.</p>

<h2>Best Solar Companies in Denver</h2>
<p>When selecting a solar installer in Denver, prioritize companies with proper Colorado licensing, extensive local experience, and strong warranty offerings. Look for installers certified by the North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners (NABCEP) and licensed electrical contractors registered with the state of Colorado. The best Denver solar companies offer comprehensive warranties including 25-year panel warranties, 10-year inverter warranties, and workmanship guarantees of at least 5-10 years. Research customer reviews and Better Business Bureau ratings, and request multiple quotes to compare pricing and equipment options. Reputable installers will provide detailed site assessments, energy production estimates, and handle all permitting and interconnection paperwork with Xcel Energy. Avoid door-to-door sales tactics and always verify the company's local presence, insurance coverage, and track record of completed installations in the Denver area.</p>

